author: Justin Hoyo
text:
Very very nice AF (I would say top 5 in Singapore)! Location is rather convenient, only a 3 minute walk form Bishan MRT station. The gym is big and very well-equipped, with dumbbells up to 50KG.

They also have 4 power racks, 1 smith machine, and 2 deadlift platforms! Treadmills were sufficient + 1x stairmaster. Toilets/changing room were also nice and clean ‚ò∫Ô∏è

author: Sihan Goi
text:
Went for a lunchtime workout on a Monday. Reached around 11 and it was quite crowded. Strangely, the crowd dissipated after a while.

Gym is quite new and has quite an extensive array of Hammer Strength and Lifefitness equipment. 4 racks (2 half and 2 cages), 2 platforms with 2 sets of bumper plates plus 2 extra pairs of 20s. 1 hybrid bar (both PL/WL knurlings) per rack/platform, and there are several metal 2.5kg collars, which are very rare in globogyms, though not very necessary outside of competition.

Not much to complain about if you're a regular gymrat or even powerlifter. However, as a weightlifter, I'd have to say that the bars are sub par. They look OK at first glance, but most of them don't spin properly. I found 2 that aren't stuck, but even then they aren't smooth. That's my biggest gripe and the main reason why it's not 5 stars. Also, the racks are setup very near one another so it's difficult to change plates because the bars are so close to one another. Lastly, the racks have very wide intervals between the hooks, so if you're unlucky, you may not find a good position.  There are also no specialty bars such as trap bars or football/Swiss bars, but that's a minor grievance.

author: a
text:
Two months back, I had the pleasure of working with Hazril , and the experience has been transformative. From our first session, it was clear that he genuinely cares about my goals and well-being. Hazril tailored a program that challenged me while still being achievable, keeping me motivated throughout our sessions.

What I appreciated most was his expertise in form and technique, which not only improved my performance but also helped prevent injuries. Hazril created a supportive and encouraging environment, pushing me to exceed my limits while celebrating my progress.

Thanks to his guidance, I've gained strength, confidence, and a deeper understanding of fitness.
